TY  - JOUR
T1  - Toward A Taxonomy of Multidimensional Constructs
AU  - Law, Kenneth S.
AU  - Wong, Chi-Sum
AU  - Mobley, William M.
Y1  - 1998/10/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1998.1255636
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1998.1255636
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 741
EP  - 755
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We propose a taxonomy of multidimensional constructs based on the relations between the construct and its dimensions. Multidimensional constructs that exist at deeper levels than their dimensions we term latent model. We call constructs formed as algebraic functions of their dimensions aggregate model, whereas constructs formed as different profiles of dimensional characteristics we term profile model. We discuss the nature of multidimensional constructs defined under these models and their operationalizations in empirical research.
AB  - We propose a taxonomy of multidimensional constructs based on the relations between the construct and its dimensions. Multidimensional constructs that exist at deeper levels than their dimensions we term latent model. We call constructs formed as algebraic functions of their dimensions aggregate model, whereas constructs formed as different profiles of dimensional characteristics we term profile model. We discuss the nature of multidimensional constructs defined under these models and their operationalizations in empirical research.
